profile_positions.description:
•	Developed and oversaw the Institutes first development-partner funded Simulation of electoral
        officials which resulted in the first ever national training program for electoral officials;
•	Assisted in the review for “Manual for Election Officials 2011”
•	publication of 2 peer reviewed scientific research manuscripts on Democracy in Africa; 
•	provided lectures, seminars, workshops and trainings for diversified groups and organizations on
        democracy and electoral management; 
•	served in the initial research team that provided the political road-map and the re-adjustment of 
        the yet to be implemented constituency boundaries in Nigeria; 
•	contributed to the growth of the Institute by serving on institutional negotiations, mediations, 
        research strategy, grants, contracting, and interview committees.

•	Responsible for POLICY Initiatives and External Relations with West African authorities and 
        institutions in developing re-integration program for West African repartees from the Netherlands;
•	Carried out extensive research on the conformity of Dutch repatriation policy to international 
       standards, especially in seeing that deportees were sent to and received in their countries of origin;
•	Set up logistic platforms for the reception and integration of deportees by creating network of 
        schools, training centres and health institutions for deportees in several West African Countries for 
        easy access to training, education and health provisions;
•	Liaised with and trained domestic NGO partners on logistics in 7 West African countries for 
        welcoming and assisting in the re-integration of deportee migrants from the Netherlands.

•	responsible for the day-to-day running of the administrative secretariat;
•	efficiently coordinated a 17-member workforce in the secretariat;
•	successfully implemented Spiritan Policy on formation, trainings, education and grassroots 
        engagement;
•	coordinated partnerships with local/international NGOs/government agencies on development 
        assistance and partnership;
•	represented the Congregation on assigned major conferences and meetings;
•	organized major events for the congregation and supervised project activities;
•	served as a link between the administration and members of the congregation both in Nigeria 
        and internationally;
•	produced "Monthly Newsletter" on Congregational events for regular information dissemination;
•	assisted in supervising major budget allocations and implementations for the congregation;
•	launched major initiatives, especially in modernizing and digitalizing administrative procedures 
       and introducing teamwork, inclusive language and inter-cultural sensitivity in the Secretariat.

•	coordinated Councils’ partnership initiative on rural development, political participation and 
        electoral mobilization; 
•	assisted in the formulation and implemenation of policy on rural development and economic 
        engagement in the municapality;
•	provided opportunity for networking, trainings and workshops for rural entrepreneurs in the 
        municipality; 
•	mobilized, trained and engaged over 250 students from 15 high schools in 
        development/economic initiatives and engagement in the municipality.
